PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FSpeaking in his parliamentary office,
OL,7,Fwith his term as an MSP due to end
OL,8,Fwhen he steps down at May's Holyrood
OL,9,Felection, Mr Ross admitted: "I know
OL,10,FI'm not everyone's cup of tea."
OL,12,FThe politician is no stranger to an
OL,13,Fargument and knows he "gets under the
OL,14,Fskin" of his opponents.
OL,16,FMr Ross told the Press Association
OL,17,Fthey were probably "punching the air"
OL,18,Fwhen he announced he was leaving ` a
OL,19,Fdecision he made three months before
OL,20,Fhe told the public.
OL,26,@qD@]OUrD@_O]uD@WOUvD@EO]yD@TOUyD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FSpeaking about his own party's
OL,7,Freaction to him quitting, he added:
OL,8,F"What my colleagues thought and what
OL,9,Fthey said to me were probably two
OL,10,Fdifferent things because everyone was
OL,11,Fvery complimentary about what I'd done.
OL,13,F"Political opponents have been fairly
OL,14,Fmuted in their response, probably
OL,15,Fpunching the air when I'm not looking.
OL,17,F"I understand that I am not everyone's
OL,18,Fcup of tea and I can get under the
OL,19,Fskin of some opposition politicians."
OL,26,@pD@AOUuD@AOUyD@AOU{D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
