PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FAsked if he could be friends with Ms
OL,7,FSturgeon, Mr Ross did not miss a beat,
OL,8,Fsaying: "No, we've got nothing in
OL,9,Fcommon."
OL,11,FFor the 43-year-old, football has been
OL,12,Fa means to overcome differences
OL,13,Fbetween him and many politicians,
OL,14,Fincluding Mr Yousaf, while he spoke to
OL,15,FMr Swinney about rural Scotland.
OL,26,@pD@IOUqD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FBut the Tory suggested the
OL,7,Ffriendliness with Scotland's current
OL,8,FFirst Minister would not last, saying:
OL,9,F"We only overlapped a little bit and
OL,10,Fhe was still at the time of being nice
OL,11,FJohn Swinney and being friends with
OL,12,Feveryone ` I remember he came up and
OL,13,Fshook my hand immediately after the
OL,14,Fvote to elect him as First Minister.
OL,16,F"So he was still trying to be as
OL,17,Fconsensual as possible but you could
OL,18,Fsee, at times, there's a bit of rage
OL,19,Funder that kind of serious bank
OL,20,Fmanager image that he quite likes."
OL,26,@qD@AOUxD@AOU|D@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FBut Mr Ross's issues are wider than
OL,7,Fthe SNP, claiming "Westminster acts
OL,8,Fmore like a parliament" than Holyrood
OL,9,Fdoes, which was part of his reason for
OL,10,Fopting to stand down ahead of seeking
OL,11,Felection at the next Westminster
OL,12,Fgeneral election.
OL,14,F"We're too scripted," he said, talking
OL,15,Fabout his fellow MSPs.
OL,17,F"It's quite a sterile environment in
OL,18,Fterms of the debating and it's the
OL,19,Fsame with questions.
OL,26,@oD@SOUpD@WO]vD@AOUvD@UO]yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,F"We see so often that a chunk of the
OL,7,FFirst Minister's Questions is
OL,8,Fdedicated to constituency and general
OL,9,Fsupplementary questions.
OL,11,F"The ones on the SNP benches, by and
OL,12,Flarge, are written by John Swinney's
OL,13,Fadvisers ` there's no doubt about it,
OL,14,Fbecause it's a subject that apparently
OL,15,Fhe knows nothing about it, but he can
OL,16,Fflip his folder and read out an answer.
OL,18,F"That's not the way it should be."
OL,20,FLike all politicians, abuse is a part
OL,21,Fof the MSP's daily life.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUzD@AOUzD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FMr Ross said: "It doesn't really
OL,7,Fbother me. What bothers me is when my
OL,8,Fwife says someone is saying this about
OL,9,Fyou, or my parents."
OL,11,FThe family part hurts, the MSP
OL,12,Fadmitted, as he recalled posting a
OL,13,Fpicture online holding his newborn.
OL,15,FHe said: "There were some very nice
OL,16,Fcomments, then there was another one,
OL,17,Fsomething like, 'oh, just another rat
OL,18,Ftaken into the world'."
OL,26,@nD@OOUqD@TO]wD@JOUzD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
