PN,30511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FWorse than the abuse, Mr Ross said,
OL,7,Fand the lowest point of his Holyrood
OL,8,Fcareer, was the failure of his Right
OL,9,Fto Recovery Bill, which was voted down
OL,10,Flast year.
OL,12,FAfter gathering with families outside
OL,13,FParliament who had lost children due
OL,14,Fto drink and drug abuse, Mr Ross said
OL,15,Fhe asked Health Secretary Neil Gray at
OL,16,Fthe coffee queue in the Garden Lobby
OL,17,Fif the Government would abstain on the
OL,18,Fvote, having told families he was
OL,19,Fhopeful they would.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FAccording to Mr Ross, Mr Gray said
OL,7,F"the answer is no".
OL,9,FThe Conservative MSP told PA: "It was
OL,10,Fat that point I knew years of hard
OL,11,Fwork from me in my office, but more
OL,12,Fimportantly decades of campaigning for
OL,13,Fchange, was going to fall that
OL,14,Fafternoon because the SNP and the
OL,15,FGreens were going to be equipped to
OL,16,Fvote down a Bill that I genuinely
OL,17,Fthink would save us.
OL,19,F"That's the worst moment I've had in
OL,20,Fthis Parliament."
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@RO]qD@_OU{D@AOU|D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771830269
OL,3,CDouglas Ross: I know I'm not
OL,4,Ceveryone's cup of tea
OL,6,FAsked for comment, a spokesperson for
OL,7,Fthe SNP said: "We wish Douglas Ross
OL,8,Fall the very best in whatever he
OL,9,Fchooses to do next ` he's shrewdly
OL,10,Fchosen to leave on his own accord,
OL,11,Fthat is not an opportunity that many
OL,12,Fof his colleagues will have."
OL,26,@oD@OOUtD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/13
